      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The climate benefits of congestion pricing are scientifically clear, as reducing vehicle miles traveled directly lowers emissions. However, the equity concerns are often used by opponents to stall progress, creating a false dichotomy. A modern, well-designed system can mitigate these issues through targeted rebates or transit subsidies, allowing the environmental necessity to drive the policy forward. Therefore, the consensus leans toward accepting the cost as a necessary investment for a sustainable urban future.",
